The paper deals with the problem of navigation for wheeled platforms using visual-inertial SLAM systems, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a new method for trajectory computation, which involves visual data processing (cs.CV) and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The proposed method also involves real-time adjustments to the trajectory, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses experimental results to validate the proposed method, which involves data analysis and statistical methods (cs.AI).
